 {"id":"bd-y9zeg","title":"add conformance harness for fscrypt legacy ioctl transport discrepancy","description":"Spec gap from FEATURE_PARITY: ext4 fscrypt nokey support is functionally present for FS_IOC_GET_ENCRYPTION_POLICY (legacy v1), but current restricted-FUSE kernels surface EIO on the mounted path because the legacy getter advertises out_size == 0 even though direct ffs-fuse dispatch succeeds. Scope: add a conformance-style harness case that exercises the same encrypted fixture through both direct dispatch and mounted-path probes, records the divergent outcomes in a stable golden/report artifact, and makes the transport-layer discrepancy mechanically auditable instead of prose-only. Acceptance: 1) harness fixture tags the requirement and expected divergence, 2) direct dispatch path proves legacy getter success payload encoding, 3) mounted path proves the current EIO transport result, 4) discrepancy is emitted in a structured compliance artifact or documented matrix entry rather than only FEATURE_PARITY prose.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T05:40:06.813895157Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-23T04:21:22.357023147Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T04:14:15.788089534Z","close_reason":"Already resolved: commit 676ae46 added the conformance harness (ext4_fscrypt_legacy_policy_transport_discrepancy_conforms in crates/ffs-harness/tests/conformance.rs:950) with structured golden artifact at conformance/golden/ext4_fscrypt_legacy_policy_transport_discrepancy.json. Direct-dispatch and mounted-path probes emit the divergent outcomes; commit dfe243d cleaned up the u64-as-u8 casts so the workspace clippy gate stays green.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","ffs-harness","fscrypt","ioctl","testing"]}
